                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.6211/371</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-04T18:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 5, 2.10 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3844. Your 2963, May 2.<note n="1" xml:id="d1079fn1">Not printed; it contained a
                        summary of developments to date in the <persName>Von Igel</persName>
                        case.</note> In this connection it may be of use to you to know that with
                    the knowledge and permission of the Foreign Office I kept a certain part of my
                    work, principally for British relief, in the old British consulate building
                    here, but nevertheless on the night of October 7, 1914, the police raided this
                    place, seized all my papers and records, and when I went there in the morning
                    the police who were still in possession informed me they were there by orders of
                    the Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
